Promotes 20+ ILIAGPT capabilities from stub to available by
providing real handlers backed by existing npm packages
(exceljs, docx, pptxgenjs, pdfkit, papaparse) and pure
TypeScript logic. Adds a minimal HTML test harness served from
the smoke server and a dedicated Playwright suite that drives a
REAL chromium browser through every category of the catalog —
"navegador real" verification the spec required.

New modules:

- server/cognitive/capabilityHandlers.ts: 23 real handlers
  + shared helpers. Each handler validates args, caps input
  size, and returns a JSON-serializable result:
    • file_generation: create_excel_workbook (exceljs),
      create_word_document (docx), create_pdf (pdfkit),
      create_powerpoint (pptxgenjs), create_code_file
    • data_analysis: describe_dataset (per-column stats +
      CSV parsing), clean_and_transform (dedupe + null
      normalization), forecast_series (exponential smoothing
      with rmse)
    • format_conversion: csv_to_excel_model (xlsx + SUM
      formulas)
    • research_synthesis: executive_summary (deterministic
      sentence ranking)
    • sub_agents: decompose_task (dependency chain)
    • connectors: list_available (static MCP registry)
    • plugins: list_marketplace
    • file_management: bulk_rename (pattern placeholders),
      organize_folder (type grouping)
    • scheduled_tasks: create_recurring + list_user_schedules
      (in-memory stores, per-user isolated)
    • projects: create_workspace + list_my_projects
    • security_governance: audit_recent_actions
    • enterprise: usage_analytics + rbac_check (role rules)
    • dispatch_mobile: queue_task
  pdfkit has no type declarations and ships CJS-only, so it's
  imported via `createRequire(import.meta.url)` to work under
  the project's ESM runtime (tsx).
  resetCapabilityHandlerStores() for test isolation.

- playwright.config.capabilities.ts: dedicated Playwright config
  that boots bert-smoke-server as its webServer on port 5174
  and runs only the cognitive-capabilities spec. Longer
  actionTimeout (15s) since xlsx/pptx generation can take a
  couple seconds in the browser test thread.

- e2e/cognitive-capabilities.spec.ts: 28 Playwright tests
  organized into 11 describes:
    1. Discovery: GET /capabilities shows 30+ descriptors
       across all 17 ILIAGPT categories, DOM updates with
       count.
    2. Always available: echo + platform_status.
    3. File generation: xlsx bytes (PK header verified
       in the browser via atob), docx bytes, pdf bytes with
       %PDF header, pptx with N slides, code file.
    4. Data analysis: describe_dataset (rows/cols mode +
       CSV mode), clean_and_transform, forecast_series.
    5. Format conversion: csv_to_excel_model.
    6. Research + sub-agents: executive_summary, decompose_task
       with dependency chain verification.
    7. Connectors + plugins.
    8. File management: bulk_rename + organize_folder with
       TWO-PHASE APPROVAL HANDSHAKE (first call returns
       approval_required + challenge token, second call with
       the token executes).
    9. State round-trips: scheduled_tasks + projects create
       then list sees the new entry, per-user isolated.
   10. Governance + enterprise: rbac_check (admin vs editor),
       audit_recent_actions, usage_analytics.
   11. Dispatch + error paths: queue_task, unknown capability,
       stub returns not_implemented, invocation landed in
       /users/:userId/runs repository.

Router changes:

- GET /api/cognitive/test-harness serves a minimal HTML page
  with window.invokeCapability() + window.listCapabilities() +
  window.resetHandlerStores() helpers for Playwright to drive
  via page.evaluate. The harness page exposes a #last-result
  <pre> and a #registry-count <div> so Playwright can also
  assert DOM state, not just network responses.

- POST /api/cognitive/test-harness/reset clears the in-memory
  capability stores between tests so state round-trip tests
  (E20/E21) are deterministic.

- Main catalog registry now uses buildCapabilityHandlerMap()
  so every handler-backed descriptor is auto-promoted from
  "stub" to "available" at boot time.

Middleware:

- Minor defensive fix to cognitiveMiddleware.invokeCapability
  so the post-invoke span attribute writes run even if
  registry.invoke somehow returns without assigning
  `invocation` (TypeScript insisted on this — never-throws
  contract holds either way).

Tests: 23 new unit tests (#238-#260) covering every handler
